hopobject.body: I'm on business healthspark.co.uk discount code A Downing Street source confirmed Cameron misspoke during a visit to Darwen, Lancashire, but insisted there is the potential for communities to have millions of pounds flowing into local coffers should the wells prove productive - in addition to an upfront payment of £100,000, one per cent of revenues from production should be paid to communities under the proposed community benefits regime. The UK Onshore Operators Group estimates this could be worth between £5m and £10m per well over 25 years.
